After suffering a disappointing 33-17 loss to LSU to start the season, the Miami Hurricanes have been rolling. The Hurricanes have a 5-1 record at the halfway point after their 28-27 comeback victory over archrival Florida State.

The Hurricanes’ defense has been among the best in college football, currently ranking second in the country at 237.3 yards per game allowed. They also have a plus-six turnover margin through six games.

summary:
“When you're comfortable in your own skin, you look beautiful, regardless of any flaws.”
But the thing is; once you’re truly...
body:
“When you’re comfortable in your own skin, you look beautiful, regardless of any flaws.”

But the thing is; once you’re truly comfortable you come to realize there really are no flaws. Whose to say what makes a flaw? To me, there is no such thing. It comes down to things that make you uniquely exquisite. It’s that color pop you bring into the world around you. Character, your body, your skin…whatever it is that you consider a “flaw” is the exact opposite. It’s true genuine depiction that separates you from everyone else. Embrace that. It’s taken me forever, and still working on it, to realize this.

I don’t wear makeup anymore unless it’s an occasion or something. I’m allowing myself to embrace every ounce of my body and its capability. I’m making sure I do everything in my power to be a good person, give, and spread any form of light. If you can rest your head at night knowing you did your best and we’re kind. You can rest assured you’re definitely not flawed. You’re simply beautiful.

Repost 📷 @themindmedic

I C R Y B E C A U S E | hats off to @tommy_mallet @towie for using his platform to shatter the stigma around male mental health. Whilst I am certainly seeing an influx of young boys and men coming to see me in clinic there is certainly a difference in the time it takes for them to present first to their GP and in turn to mental health services. Quite often they are much further down the line compared to their female counterparts. Suicide remains the biggest killer in our young men. Something has got to give. #icrybecause #Repost @tommy_mallet with @get_repost
・・・
Thanks everyone for all of your messages over the last few weeks they mean a lot. I’ve had a tough few months but wanna use my experience to help people so I am going to kick off this movement with #ICryBecause sometimes it gets too much. This is for anyone out there who feels the same and just lettin you all know it’s okay not to be okay. Good morning.

Yes, I’m superstitious about what I wear when I run. Lucky everything.

Today I realized I’ve been running 4-6 days a week for the last month. The love of my life and I are starting to reconnect. We drifted apart, but I have my body to thank for reintroducing us. I think it’s going to be a life-long relationship ♥️ (I’m talking about running) I love you, running.

Happy Tuesday

Xx
